EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO TAXATION -- STATE TAX OFFICIALS
***
1 This act would cap the interest rate for all delinquent taxes at twelve percent (12%). This
2 act would also limit the tax administrator’s authority to audit taxpayers to three (3) years from the
3 date of the tax filing. For fraudulent returns, the audit period shall not exceed seven (7) years, and
4 no audit can be performed beyond ten (10) years.
5 This act would take effect on January 1, 2026, and would apply to all assessments, audits
6 and tax payments, including delinquent taxes, initiated on or after this date
